&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated and quality focused Senior Data Engineer to join our Data Engineering team to design, build, and maintain reliable and scalable data pipelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a strong Python/PySpark developer equally comfortable with writing code and helping business teams understand data. A self-starter, comfortable with ambiguity, ability to think big (while paying careful attention to detail) and enjoy working in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Take On&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop and maintain high-capacity and scalable data pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop and maintain API based ETL/ELT processes for raw data collection from multiple sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build and maintain data products through its release cycle including building data pipelines, curating the data sets for building in KPIs, and designing accompanying data quality and observability layer.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build advanced semantic layers, establish rigorous data validation, data lineage tracking, and performance-monitoring frameworks to ensure delivery of quality data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide thought leadership and collaborate with other team members to continue to scale our architecture to evolve for the needs of tomorrow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and support continuous integration build and deployment processes using Jenkins, Docker, Git, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and implement monitoring and alerting policies for data solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of hands-on experience in Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience with Databricks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of hands-on experience in using advanced SQL queries and writing/optimizing highly efficient SQL queries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience integrating with 3rd party APIs is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience of working in AWS environment is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in front-end technologies, including JavaScript, CSS3 and/or HTML5 and frameworks such as React Js, Node, Angular, Vue.js and/or jQuery is highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with business customers to collect requirements and gain a deep understanding of varied business domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in testing and monitoring data for anomalies and rectifying them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing and building ontologies, advanced semantic layers, taxonomies, or knowledge graphs is highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of software coding practices across the development lifecycle, including agile methodologies, coding standards, code reviews, source management, build processes, testing, and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
